title: For Sale/Trade:  1953 Swiss Schmidt-Rubin K31 w/walnut stock Troop Tag  7.5 Swiss
postcontent: Contact: text or call Nine28-Two66-3six26, email is ok tooThis Rifle is a very rare K31. The rife is rare because the action including all the metal parts are dated in 1953 which is a later post-war production. Yet the stock is a beatiful walnut stock dated back in 1944. as you K31 collectors out there, you know that later production K31 usually have Beech wood stock. However, all the wood parts' serial number on the rifle match with the ones on the action. I have digged into the history of this and found this.According to http://www.cruffler.com/study, when they were manufacturing the rifle on 1953, they found several batches of unused war-time walnut stocks inside a cave. So they decided to use those stocks on these new productions. therefore, u have a 1953 produced K31 with a 1944 walnut stock in front of you. Also i found a troop tag right under the butt plate. This is a highly collectable K31 that is full of history.All the numbers are matching even includes the the upper handguard and the stock. Yes, I did take it fully disassembled in order to clean it so I have looked at the wood parts' serial number.
